tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE game_analytics (
    game_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    game_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    total_players INT,
    active_players INT,
    game_duration TIME,
    revenue DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE performance_metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    game_id INT,
    level_name VARCHAR(50),
    completion_rate DECIMAL(5, 2),
    play_time_minutes INT
);

CREATE TABLE GameAnalytics (
    game_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    game_title VARCHAR(255),
    total_players INT,
    revenue DECIMAL,
    playtime_hours FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE PlayerInteractions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    game_id INT,
    player_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE PerformanceMetrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    game_id INT,
    average_fps FLOAT,
    memory_usage INT,
    cpu_utilization DECIMAL,
    storage_capacity INT
);

CREATE TABLE games (
    game_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    game_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    developer_id UUID REFERENCES game_developers(developer_id),
    release_date DATE,
    genre TEXT,
    platform TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE player_data (
    player_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    game_id UUID REFERENCES games(game_id),
    player_name TEXT,
    playtime_hrs INT,
    level INT,
    last_played DATE
);

CREATE TABLE game_metrics (
    metric_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    game_id UUID REFERENCES games(game_id),
    active_players INT,
    daily_revenue FLOAT,
    total_downloads INT,
    average_rating FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE games (game_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  game_title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  release_date DATE,
  genre VARCHAR(100),
  developer_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (developer_id) REFERENCES developers(developer_id))

CREATE TABLE players (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE,
  country VARCHAR(50),
  registration_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE game_sessions (session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  player_id INT,
  game_id INT,
  session_date DATE,
  duration_minutes INT,
  score INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (player_id) REFERENCES players(player_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (game_id) REFERENCES games(game_id))

CREATE TABLE game_events (event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  event_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  event_type VARCHAR(50),
  event_date DATE,
  player_id INT,
  game_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (player_id) REFERENCES players(player_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (game_id) REFERENCES games(game_id))

CREATE TABLE developers (developer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  developer_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  founding_date DATE,
  headquarters_location VARCHAR(100))
